      • exec

        public boolean exec(CommandWrapper command)
        Attempts to find and execute a ShortCommand based on the provided CommandWrapper

        If a command with a matching name is found, the command is executed and the method returns true. If the command is not found, the method returns false. This class is strictly for internal command handling, and should not be used under any circumstances

        Parameters:
        command - The CommandWrapper created from a server command
        Returns:
        Whether or not the command ran successfully
        See Also:
        CommandWrapper
